Anzac
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:2
Definition:Anzac Cove, Anzac Peninsula
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: [Fraser and Gibbons 1925 (Soldier and Sailor Words 8) note that `ANZAC COVE: The name given to the Anzacs' landing place at Gallipoli to commemorate the heroism displayed on the occasion. Anzac Cove was so named by General Birdwood.']
